ere $\\lambda \\approx$ 1 fm and $<k_T^2> \\approx$ 1 GeV$^2$ is the average\ntransverse kick-squared received by the parton per collision. The energy loss\nper collision at the $\\sqrt{s_\\textrm{NN}}$ =2.76 TeV is found to be about\ntwice of that at 0.2 TeV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Feb 2011 04:31:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Mar 2011 04:28:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-27"}
